{"type":null,"faqId":47101,"title":"How do I use smart unlock?","answer":"<p>Smart unlock makes unlocking your phone a breeze. Simply bring your Bluetooth device within range of your phone and press the power key to unlock. No password is required. <span style=\"COLOR: black\">To use smart unlock, you will need a supported Huawei phone and a Bluetooth-enabled device, such as a headset or wristband. The steps for enabling smart unlock with a Bluetooth headset are as follows: </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"COLOR: black\">1. Open <b>Settings</b> and select <b>Screen lock &amp; passwords</b>. Select <b>Password</b> and enter a password (skip this step if you already have a password). </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"COLOR: black\">2. Open <b>Settings</b> and select <b>Screen lock &amp; passwords</b>. Select <b>Smart unlock</b>, as shown below: </span></p>\n<p> <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman','serif'; FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><img width=\"179\" height=\"316\" src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=SupportImage&imagePath=/20151015174408275001.jpg\"></span>  <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman','serif'; FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><img width=\"181\" height=\"316\" src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=SupportImage&imagePath=/20151015174433869001.jpg\"></span>  <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman','serif'; FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><img width=\"178\" height=\"317\" src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=SupportImage&imagePath=/20151015174447832001.jpg\"></span> </p>\n<p>&nbsp;3. Enter your screen unlock password to enter the smart unlock settings screen. Connect your Bluetooth device as shown below: </p>\n<p> <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman','serif'; FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><img width=\"171\" height=\"304\" src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=SupportImage&imagePath=/20151015174541224001.jpg\"></span>  <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman','serif'; FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><img width=\"175\" height=\"309\" src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=SupportImage&imagePath=/20151015174558179001.jpg\"></span>  <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman','serif'; FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><img width=\"179\" height=\"314\" src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=SupportImage&imagePath=/20151015174612435001.jpg\"></span> </p>\n<p>&nbsp;4.<span style=\"COLOR: black\"> Select </span><b>Add a Bluetooth device</b>, enable <b><span style=\"COLOR: black\">Smart unlock</span></b> and then select the Bluetooth device you connected during Step 3 as shown below: </p>\n<p> <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman','serif'; FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><img width=\"188\" height=\"326\" src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=SupportImage&imagePath=/20151015174659555001.jpg\"></span> </p>\n<p>&nbsp;5. <span style=\"COLOR: black\">Once configured</span>, you can unlock your phone using a Bluetooth device when it is in range. </p>\n<p><span>Note: When more than one Bluetooth device is connected to your phone, all devices can use the smart unlock feature. </span></p>","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":0,"unUseful":0,"languageId":242,"languageName":"id","faqCode":"2601","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"0","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1444902474000,"seriesProductName":"CRR-L13","visitedTimes":20,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":null,"filePath":null,"imagePath":null,"imageName":null,"productIdList":null,"curPage":null,"pageSize":null,"siteCode":null,"statusFlag":"Publish","returnCode":0,"totalRows":null,"keywords":null,"avgScore":0.0,"createDate":null,"totalPages":null}